fields.name: Mimosa
fields.description: Mimosa, also known as "Purple Mimosa," is a hybrid marijuana strain made by crossing Clementine with Purple Punch. In small doses, this strain produces happy, level-headed effects that will leave you feeling uplifted and motivated enough to take on any mundane task. In large doses, Mimosa may make you feel sleepy and relaxed. This strain has a strong aroma and flavor that reminds you of its namesake, with notes of fruit and citrus flavors bursting through. Medical marijuana patients choose this strain to help relieve symptoms associated with depression and stress. Mimosa is a staple from the Tangie family.
fields.grow_info: Mimosa is an indica/sativa variety from Symbiotic Genetics and can be cultivated indoors (where the plants will need a flowering time of ▒60 days) and outdoors. Symbiotic Genetics' Mimosa is a THC dominant variety and is/was never available as feminized seeds.

fields.name: Honey Bananas
fields.lineage: Strawberry Banana x Honey Boo Boo
fields.description: Honey Bananas from Elemental Seeds is a heavy-handed hybrid strain bred from Strawberry Banana and Honey Boo Boo. This cannabis strain earns its name with a resinous coat as sticky as honey and an unmistakable banana aroma. She tends to provide weighty full-body effects coupled with an invigorating buzz of cerebral euphoria.
fields.grow_info:
Honey Bananas is a mostly indica variety from Elemental Seeds and can be cultivated indoors (where the plants will need a flowering time of ▒60 days) and outdoors. Elemental Seeds' Honey Bananas is a THC dominant variety and is/was only available as feminized seeds.

Honey Bananas from Elemental Seeds is a very sweet and frosty female that is easy on the eye and heavy in potency. Made from a Honey Boo and Strawberry Bananas cross, she tantalizes your senses. Lovers of intense Indicas will be overjoyed with their bunch of Honey Bananas - inducing a deep penetrative stone; that comes bundled with a mild mind buzz.

Plucked from the elite marijuana ranks of Elemental Seeds, Honey Bananas is a sweet and satisfying feminized creation that boasts a unique character and immense desirability . Very much a plant of genetic complexity, she is derived from a Honey Boo and Strawberry Bananas cross - extracting the best traits from both of her flavorful parents.
Mostly Indica in nature, she grows with vigor and pace - flowering (on average) between 58 and 63 days. Just as her name suggests, Honey Bananas is rife with the sweet and fruity notes - the most noticeable of which being bananas. After completing her manageable flowering period, Honey Bananas rewards breeders with delectable harvests; consisting of dank buds that are smothered in a frosty blanket of resin. These sensational harvests are large in size but even larger in quality.
Honey Bananas not only appeals to sweet-toothed smokers, but also cannabis connoisseurs, cultivators and collectors alike. Once you're lured in by her tasty salad of summer fruits, Honey Bananas then induces a highly stimulating body buzz; one that also takes hold of your mind. The perfect marijuana strain for relaxing with friends or
When it comes to harvests, Honey Bananas is a high yielding machine. Gazing upon your majestic mound of marijuana makes all the work totally worth it.

fields.name: Island Sweet Skunk
fields.description: Island Sweet Skunk is a sativa marijuana strain made by crossing Sweet Pink Grapefruit with Skunk #1. This strain is often enjoyed for its energetic and uplifting effects. Island Sweet Skunk (sometimes known as Sweet Island Skunk) offers a sweet, skunky flavor with undertones of grapefruit. This strain also comes in a CBD variety to help medical marijuana patients treat symptoms associated with chronic anxiety, inflammation and muscle spasms. This strain comes in buds that are green with bright yellow and orange hairs.
fields.grow_info:
*AWARD WINNING STRAIN*

Our strongest smelling strain and one of our most powerful. Heavy yielding strain that will keep getting bigger and bigger. Long spear like colas that need to be tied up or staked in the last few weeks due to excessive weight. Sativa dominant growth structure with a sweat inducing stone. No vegetation time needed for sea of green. Consumer favorite, most bang for the buck. Indoor only BC. - great when force flowered in a greenhouse in B.C.

Finishes great outdoors below the 40th parallel.

Indoors: 9 weeks
Outdoors: Mid to late October

fields.name: French Macaron
fields.description: French Macaron is an indica dominant hybrid strain (70% indica/30% sativa) create through crossing the delicious Gelato 33 X French Cookies strains. Best known for its amazingly mouthwatering flavor, French Macaron is a great option for any indica lover who's looking for a super tasty toke. Like its name suggests, French Macaron has a sweet and sugary nutty cookie flavor with hints of fresh fruits and just a touch of lightly tangy lemon. The aroma is just as amazing, with a nutty cookie overtone accented by fresh sweet cream, sour citrus a hint of dank. The French Macaron high is just as delightful, with a happy and soothing overtone that hits both mind and body with a high level of potency. You'll feel euphoric and creatively inspired, easily jumping on art projects or chatting with those around you. A lightly relaxing physical high accompanies this heady state, helping you to stay anchored while also inspiring a pretty heavy of the munchies. Combined with its high 20-23% average THC level, these effects make French Macaron a great choice for treating those suffering from conditions such as chronic stress or anxiety, mood swings or depression and appetite loss or nausea. This bud has long pepper-shaped olive green nugs with lots of thin orange hairs and a coating of frosty, purple-tinted white crystal trichomes.
fields.grow_info:
The structure of the French Macaron flower is a beautiful marriage of Gelato 33 x French Cookies, expressing some of the best traits from each parent. French Macaron's tightly packed calyxes erupt with so many trichomes, it can be hard to see the beautiful, tight, dark purple bud underneath. Aromas of gas, musk and heavy cream come together reminiscent of a sweet, creamy dessert. Until now French Macaron's first and only appearance has been at the 2017 Expo Grow in Ir·n, immediately winning in the Indica category. Now finally available for everyone who is eager to discover this next level crystal covered Cookies powerhouse.

TYPE: Mostly Indica
GENETICS: Gelato 33 x French Cookies
YIELD: 500gr - 600gr p.s.m.
HEIGHT: 90cm - 110cm
FLOWERING TIME: 9 Weeks
MEDICINAL CONDITIONS: Stress / Pain Relief / Depression

fields.name: Ghost Cookies
fields.lineage: Ghost OG x Girl Scout Cookies
fields.description:
Ghost Cookies is a mostly indica hybrid created by Bend, Oregon-based breeders Deschutes Growery. This strain is a cross between the staple Girl Scout Cookies and Ghost OG, a genetic combination that yields large, colorful flowers with a subtly sweet aroma. Ghost Cookies also offers a deeply relaxing body high. Its THC content has been measured at levels of between 19% and 23%.

When properly cured, Ghost Cookies gives off a nutty, toasty aroma redolent of parent strain GSC. A deeper whiff may pick up on some sweet, fruity bass notes as well. Grinding up or cracking open these flowers, on the other hand, reveals their Kush lineage with a hashy, peppery kick. When Ghost Cookies is combusted in a pipe or a joint, it burns with a heavy but pleasantly smooth and easily ingested smoke. This smoke tastes earthy with some fruity accents on the exhale.

As with many other indica-dominant strains, Ghost CookiesÆ high can be a creeper, taking 10 or 15 minutes to manifest after users have finished smoking. At first, it exercises a lightheaded feeling that may be accompanied by some flushing in the cheeks or a constricted, ôheadbandö-like feeling around the temples. As they adjust to these strange sensations, though, smokers are submerged in a dreamy, trippy headspace. External stimuli may become subject to weird distortions like a flattening of visual depth perspective; consumers also report psychedelic phenomena like a sense of time moving more slowly. Those who are so inclined can maximize these hazy properties by listening to some moody music or watching a visually engaging movie. Alternatively, Ghost Cookies can provide a great backdrop for buzzy social situations, facilitating easy conversation and good vibes. Other than these sensory experiences, though, Ghost Cookies doesnÆt do much to stimulate the mind and may not be the right choice for those looking to maintain productivity or concentration.

A dynamic all-purpose smoke, Ghost Cookies is worth seeking out by indica fans. Its deeply sedative effects make it the perfect way to wind down after a long day.
fields.grow_info:
Flowers of Ghost Cookies are typically larger than average and adhere in chunky, almost spherical clusters. The internal structure of these buds leans more indica, with a solid center made up of wide, closely-coiled leaves. These leaves themselves are a dappled mix of dark forest green and deep indigo, with the latter hues coming about thanks to high concentrations of the pigment anthocyanin in the strainÆs genetics. Finally, bright orange pistils and translucent, milky trichomes finish off these already-colorful flowers.

Unfortunately for those looking to grow it at home, seeds of Ghost Cookies have not been cultivated for commercial sale. Instead, prospective gardeners can seek out clippings from mature, healthy plants of the strain; these can be propagated as ôclonesö and may be grown indoors or out. While there isnÆt much specific information available on cultivating this strain, its indica-looking flowers imply that plants grow short and squat and that they have a relatively short flowering time of between 8 and 9 weeks.

fields.name: Peach Pie
fields.description:
The Peach Pie strain is as fruity-delicious as you would expect, and it comes with euphoric, rushing, blissful effects to back it up. Even the smoke is sweet on this strain, which has an appealing terpene profile that it inherited from its parents, Rainbow Pie and Dozizoz. This means that Peach Pie has Zkittlez genetics on both of its parentsÆ sides, so fans of that strain should know what to expect when they take a slice of the new one for their afternoon relaxation session.

Peach Pie leans towards Indica, though the exact proportion has not been reported, and has a THC level of around 18.5% on average. It was bred by Green Fire Genetics out of Mendocino, California, the same folks who made Green Fire OG and Dozizoz. Its primary terpene is limonene, and this comes with grapefruit, peach, and citrus flavors. The strain starts out sweet and transforms into something more spicy-tart as linalool and beta-caryophyllene start to come out. The smoke is smooth and sweet, completing the appeal of a strain that makes you feel heavy and physically grounded with an airy aroma.

As for its effects, the strain is known for being sedating, so consumers are advised to watch their activity levels and try as hard as possible to do as little as possible while high on Peach Pie. We recommend pairing your pie with a date at the spa, a great movie or TV show marathon, catching up on your video games, catching up on your sleep, or doing nothing at all.

The result of all these flavors is a strain that has the effect of a euphoric rush that comes on fast and strong, uplifting and relaxing your body. As a physically sedating strain, it dulls your senses, relaxes the stomach, and puts your day in a full-on happy slump. The experience is heavy, body-altering, sweet and tart. The flavors of citrus and peach create a bright, smooth experience that turns you into the opposite û dull and faded in the best possible way.

If youÆre looking for relaxed bliss as a major Zkittlez fan or youÆre just planning a low-key afternoon movie marathon and want to absorb it properly, Peach Pie will be there for you, as only pie can.
fields.grow_info:
The buds of the Peach Pie strain are dense and shaped vaguely like little teardrops. TheyÆre deep green and purple in color, with a ton of trichome fuzz, peppered with peach-colored pistils. The strain smells funky and bright even while itÆs still in the ground, with a flavor tinged with minty coolness and a little tart fuel flavor at the end.

Peach Pie is a hybrid cross of one of our select phenos of Rainbow Pie (aka: Zkittlez x Grand Blueberry Pie) hit with our Dozizoz stud (aka: Zkittlez x (Zozizoz aka: Dosidos x ZOZ BX Zkittlez) creating this candied peach rings followed by a creamy dosi zkittlez terpene profile.

fields.name: Purple Mountain Majesty
fields.description:
Depending on its genetics, Purple Mountain Majesty is considered the purple phenotype of Train Wreck, making it somewhat of a æunicornÆ or rare strain. Purple Mountain Majesty has a uniquely sweet smell and taste, mixed with notes of fresh pine. Its effects are evenly balanced, helping to provide gentle relief for both body and mind. As a balanced hybrid strain, Purple Mountain Majesty can be a wonderful choice for any time of day, whether thatÆs starting your morning with a journal entry or watching your favorite TV show in the evening.

Medical marijuana patients often choose Purple Mountain Majesty when dealing with symptoms associated with anxiety, pain, and stress. Bred by Humboldt Seed Co., Purple Mountain Majesty features flavors like violet, diesel, and blue cheese. The dominant terpene of this strain is pinene.
fields.grow_info:
Purple Mountain Majesty was first cultivated by Humboldt Seed Co. (Humboldt County, CA) in the early 2000s. It is a cross of Train Wreck, a renowned sativa-dominant strain known for its potency, and Blueberry Muffin, a uniquely sweet indica-dominant strain.

A purple train wreck phenotype unlocked when we crossed Train Wreck with the original Blueberry Muffin. We knew it was a "unicorn" from the beginning. An excessively wide growth pattern will fill your garden past the point of reason, but not to worry - she is extremely resistant to Powdery mildew and bud rot. Its signature turpentine smell comes in part from high levels of Terpinolene.

60% Indica - 40% Sativa
Flowering time: 55 days, Sept. 25 - Oct. 10

Crossed of Trainwreck and Blueberry Muffin.
Vigorous wide growth, excessively wide growth pattern.
Extremely resistant to powdery mildew and bud rot.
Signature turpentine smell comes in part from high levels of Terpinolene.
Pleasant calming effects.
